eNCA has reliably been informed that Herman Mashaba will resign as Joburg Mayor this morning. Editor's note:  This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg Mayor Herman Mashaba announced his resignation on Monday morning. It follows the Democratic Alliance's Federal Council meeting over the weekend where former party leader Helen Zille was elected chairperson. Mashaba has said far-right wingers have infiltrated the DA. Zille says Mashaba may be worried that his position could be terminated, but she says she has no power to interfere in The City of Johannesburg. 